where to begin even the bread and butter served to each table is utterly delicious located conveniently in the downtown uptown the restaurant exuded southern hospitality the smell of fried everything wafted from the kitchen sign posters on the walls showed pretty much every stage actor ever had stopped in and the staff was friendly as could be as for the food there was absolutely nothing that feel short of expectations fried tomatoes mmm mmm mmm green beans cooked in delicious country ham juices fried chicken salivating good GOODREVIEW our waitress kept emphasizing desserts we went ahead and got some strawberry shortcake a sweet explosion of flavor later we exited satisfied with smiles on our faces and about 5 pounds heavier
